cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about using convolutional neural networks to detect colorized images. The most relevant sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which deals with image processing and analysis. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.MM (Machine Learning) and cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of generalization, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
